Paper: hep-th/9801064

Date: 1998-01-12

Title: Effectiveness of One-dimensional gas models for black holes

Authors: A. Ghosh (CERN)

Comments: 14 pages, Latex, misprints corrected, reference added and minor

changes madeJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B425 (1998) 269-276

A one-dimensional gas model has been constructed and shown to provide correctexpressions for entropies for extremal and near-extremal BTZ black holes.Recently suggested boosting of black strings is used to compute the entropy forthe Schwarzschild black hole also from this gas model.